                            </addrLine>
                        </address>
                    <salute>Dear <persName key="Silvers, Earl Reed" from="1891" to="1948"
                            role="Director, War Service Bureau" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/68516378"
                            >Mr. Silvers</persName>:-</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have sent your letter to <persName key="Voorhees, Juliana Deyo" from="1880"
                        to="1956" role="Spouse" ref="https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/130099011"
                        >Mrs. Voorhees</persName>, &amp; you will probably hear from her
                    directly.</p>
                <p>The only picture of <persName key="Voorhees, John Brownlee" from="1875" to="1919"
                        role="Minister" ref="https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/130098973">Dr.
                        Voorhees</persName> in my possession is also a picture of his first baby!
                    This would hardly suit your purpose. Let me know if you are unsuccessful in
                    hearing from Mrs. Voorhees.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am <lb/> Yours very truly,</salute><lb/>
                    <signed><persName key="Berg, Irving Husted" role="Minister" from="1878"
                            to="1941" ref="http://www.jstor.org/stable/23135271">Irving H.
                            Berg</persName></signed>
                </closer>
